A process manager is just a pure function from a domain event to zero or one commands. Keep it stateless when the outgoing command can be derived from the event alone; let the command handler enforce invariants. Events the saga does not care about return `null` instead of throwing, so the feed runner can keep moving. The thin dispatcher uses appendToStream with expectedRevision to emit the next command event.

```typescript
